First Lady Melania Trump recently had a conversation with Mrs. Sophie Grégoire Trudeau of Canada. During the conversation, First Lady Trump expressed her well wishes for Mrs. Grégoire Trudeau's good health after recovering from COVID-19. She also reiterated her appreciation for the ongoing cooperation between the United States and Canada in addressing the challenges posed by the pandemic. The two leaders discussed the importance of the strong economic ties between the two countries, including the recent restrictions on non-essential travel while keeping the border open for essential workers and daily trade in goods worth $1.7 billion. They also acknowledged the extensive efforts to repatriate Americans and Canadians from cruise ships and other locations globally. Both leaders agreed to stay in touch as they work together to overcome the pandemic.